  "issue_number": 3022,
  "issue_title": "Implement the Meld keyword action (CR 701.42 / CR 712.4)",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\nThe **Meld** keyword action is not implemented at runtime. Meld cards are recognized only as a\n**card layout** (`CardLayout::Meld(front, back)`, `types/card.rs:235`) \u2014 there is **no `Effect::Meld`,\nno `perform_meld`, and no meld runtime** (`grep -r \"Effect::Meld\\|perform_meld\" crates/` is empty).\nAs a result, meld pairs cannot meld into their combined permanent, and the instigator halves parse\nto `Effect::Unimplemented`.\n\n## What meld is (CR, verified against `docs/MagicCompRules.txt`)\n- **CR 701.42a** \u2014 \"To meld the two cards in a meld pair, put them onto the battlefield with their\n  back faces up and combined. The resulting permanent is a single object represented by two cards.\"\n- **CR 701.42b/c** \u2014 only two cards of the same meld pair can meld; if they can't (e.g. a token copy),\n  they stay in their current zone.\n- **CR 712.4a/b** \u2014 the back faces (exposed in card-data as the named *result* card) determine the\n  melded permanent's characteristics.\n- **CR 712.4c** \u2014 meld cards cannot transform.\n- **CR 712.21** \u2014 when a melded permanent leaves, the two cards return to the appropriate zone (as\n  their **front** faces).\n\n## Affected cards (7 meld pairs \u2014 all 7 meld clauses confirmed in `card-data.json`)\nEach pair has one **instigator** half carrying the meld ability that names the partner and the result.\n\n| Instigator (ability form) | Partner | Melds into | Set |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Gisela, the Broken Blade (**triggered**, end step) | Bruna, the Fading Light | Brisela, Voice of Nightmares | EMN |\n| Graf Rats (**triggered**, begin combat) | Midnight Scavengers | Chittering Host | EMN |\n| Hanweir Battlements (**activated**, mana+tap) | Hanweir Garrison | Hanweir, the Writhing Township | EMN |\n| Urza, Lord Protector (**activated**, `{7}`, sorcery-speed) | The Mightstone and Weakstone | Urza, Planeswalker | BRO/MOM |\n| Mishra, Claimed by Gix (**triggered**, combat + ETB rider) | Phyrexian Dragon Engine | Mishra, Lost to Phyrexia | MOM |\n| Titania, Voice of Gaea (**triggered**, upkeep + extra condition) | Argoth, Sanctum of Nature | Titania, Gaea Incarnate | MOM |\n| Vanille, Cheerful l'Cie (**triggered**, optional cost) | (FF partner) | Ragnarok, Divine Deliverance | FIN |\n\nThe instigator halves are currently **unsupported** because the meld effect cannot be expressed.\n\n## Current behavior\nThe meld clause (\"\u2026exile them, then meld them into Z\") has no typed effect and parses to\n`Effect::Unimplemented`; the melded permanent (Brisela, Chittering Host, etc.) can never be created.\n\n## Correct behavior\nResolving the meld ability \u2014 when its controller **both owns and controls** both pair halves\n(CR 701.42b) \u2014 exiles both and puts a single melded permanent onto the battlefield, represented by\nthe two cards, with the **result card's** characteristics. Because the permanent **enters the\nbattlefield** (CR 701.42a), its **ETB abilities trigger** \u2014 this is the opposite of Mutate\n(CR 730.2b, which explicitly does *not* enter). When the melded permanent leaves, the two cards\nreturn to the appropriate zone as their **front** faces (CR 712.21).\n\n## Design (reuse the Mutate/merge single-object infrastructure \u2014 `game/merge.rs`)\nMeld is the twin of **Mutate** (\"single object represented by multiple cards\", CR 730 \u2248 CR 712), so\nmost of the hard infrastructure already exists and should be reused, **not reinvented**:\n\n- `GameObject.merged_components` \u2014 the single-object / multi-card identity.\n- `merge::split_merged_permanent_on_leave` (CR 712.21) \u2014 already returns components as their **front\n  faces** on leave; its docstring even cites the meld worked example. **Reuse as-is \u2014 no new leave code.**\n- The merge layer-1 `CopyValues` install (`merge::install_merge_layer_effect`) \u2014 but with a\n  **meld-specific copiable-values builder whose source is the result card** (e.g. Brisela), not a\n  topmost component. This is the one real divergence from Mutate.\n- Meld is **deterministic** (no top/bottom choice) \u2192 unlike Mutate it needs **no new `WaitingFor` /\n  frontend round-trip**.\n\n### \u26a0\ufe0f Implementation gotchas (these are non-obvious and will bite a naive attempt)\n1. **The effect resolver has no `CardDatabase`.** `resolve_effect(state, ability, events)` cannot\n   look up the result card by db. Use the **Conjure pattern**: resolve the result `CardFace` from\n   `state.card_face_registry` (keyed by `name.to_lowercase()`), and **seed the result name** into\n   that registry at init by adding an `Effect::Meld { result, .. } => out.push(result.clone())` arm\n   to `walk_effect` (`printed_cards.rs`).\n2. **Characteristics must be LAYER-ONLY.** Do **not** apply the result face to the survivor's *base*\n   fields (`apply_card_face_to_object` overwrites `base_*`). Build `CopiableValues` from the result\n   `CardFace` and install them purely through the layer-1 copy effect (mirroring `merge_object_onto`'s\n   never-touch-base discipline). If you corrupt the survivor's base, it returns to the graveyard as\n   **the result card instead of its own front face** \u2014 a CR 712.21 / 712.4b violation.\n3. **Synthesis has no db either** (`synthesize_all(&mut CardFace)` runs during ingestion). Let the\n   **parser** build the gated triggered/activated ability + `Effect::Meld`; keep any\n   `database/meld.rs` synthesis hook thin.\n4. **CR 712.4c transform guard needs a typed marker, not `merged_components.len() == 2`** \u2014 a\n   two-creature Mutate also has `len() == 2` and would be wrongly blocked from transforming. Add a\n   typed discriminator (e.g. `merge_kind: Option<MergeKind>` with `MergeKind { Mutate, Meld }`),\n   set it in the respective resolvers, and key the guard on `Some(MergeKind::Meld)`.\n\n### Proposed file plan\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `types/ability.rs` | `Effect::Meld { partner: String, result: String }` (no-target leaf \u2014 mirror every `Effect::Encore` match arm, **including the cross-crate `phase-ai/src/policies/redundancy_avoidance.rs` one**) |\n| `parser/oracle_effect/` (NEW combinator) | Recognize the gate (\"you both own and control \\<self\\> and a \\<type\\> named \\<partner\\>\" \u2192 `TriggerCondition::And` of two `ControlCount` own+control conjuncts) and the clause (\"exile them, then meld them into \\<result\\>\") \u2014 **nom combinators, partner-noun parameterized over card type** (creature/land/artifact), no verbatim string match |\n| `game/meld.rs` (NEW, runtime) | `perform_meld`: CR 701.42b own+control validation (CR 701.42c no-op if illegal), exile both, enter via normal `move_to_zone` (ETB fires), layer-only result characteristics, `merge_kind = Meld` |\n| `printed_cards.rs` | `meld_copiable_values(result_face)` builder + the `walk_effect` registry-seed arm |\n| `game/game_object.rs` | typed `MergeKind` marker + serde-default field, cleared on battlefield exit |\n| `game/transform.rs` | CR 712.4c guard keyed on `MergeKind::Meld` |\n| `game/effects/mod.rs` | dispatch `Effect::Meld { .. } => perform_meld(...)` |\n| `database/meld.rs` (NEW) | thin synthesis parity hook |\n| tests (separate `*_tests.rs`) | building-block tests (below) |\n| frontend | oversized melded-result display \u2014 **deferred** |\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Gisela's end-step trigger melds Bruna + Gisela into Brisela when their controller owns **and**\n      controls both; the result is a single permanent with Brisela's characteristics.\n- [ ] Hanweir Battlements' activated ability melds the pair into Hanweir, the Writhing Township.\n- [ ] The intervening-if condition (own **and** control both pair members) gates the meld correctly\n      both ways.\n- [ ] The melded permanent **enters the battlefield** and its ETB abilities fire (CR 701.42a /\n      CR 603.6a; contrast Mutate CR 730.2b).\n- [ ] When the melded permanent leaves, the two cards return as their **front** faces (reusing\n      `split_merged_permanent_on_leave`; CR 712.21).\n- [ ] Meld cards cannot transform (CR 712.4c), without breaking Mutate permanents' ability to transform.\n- [ ] Building-block tests on pair/result derivation and the meld runtime (exile-both \u2192 single melded\n      permanent; leave-split \u2192 front faces; gate both ways; cannot-transform), **not** single-card replay.\n\n## Scope / phased delivery\nThe instigator class has ~7 structural shapes. The **first pass should ship the three\nstraightforward shapes** \u2014 end-step trigger (Gisela), begin-combat trigger (Graf Rats), and\nmana+tap activated land (Hanweir Battlements) \u2014 with the partner-noun parameterized so land/artifact\ninstigators parse. The remaining shapes are **deferred** (each needs extra surface):\n- **Urza** \u2014 \"Activate only as a sorcery\" timing restriction.\n- **Mishra** \u2014 combat-state gate + the \"It enters tapped and attacking\" result-ETB rider + \"them\" phrasing.\n- **Titania** \u2014 an additional \"four or more land cards in your graveyard\" intervening-if conjunct.\n- **Vanille** \u2014 \"you may pay {cost}. If you do, \u2026\" optional-cost wrapper.\n\n## Deferrals (strict-failure / follow-up)\n- **CR 701.42c** token-copy / illegal-meld \"stay in current zone\" edge case.\n- Frontend oversized-card polish (render result-card stats first).\n- The four deferred instigator shapes above.\n\n## Notes for review\nRecommend running `engine-planner` \u2192 `review-engine-plan` before implementation \u2014 the four gotchas\nabove (registry seeding, layer-only characteristics, db-less synthesis, typed transform marker) and\nthe ETB-fires distinction are easy to get wrong and only surface under adversarial review or runtime\ntesting.\n",
